The paper discusses feature selection algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. The focus is on evaluating the performance of these algorithms in a controlled experimental scenario using synthetic problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Mining (cs.DM), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
